The paper proposes a framework for neural architecture search, which is a subfield of machine learning. Specifically, the paper focuses on using Bayesian optimization to guide network morphism for efficient neural architecture search. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper also involves optimization algorithms, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
